'''Devon Joseph Werkheiser''' (born [[March 8]], [[1991]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[actor]]. He is perhaps best known for his starring role as [[Ned Bigby]] on [[Nickelodeon (TV channel)|Nickelodeon]]'s [[situation comedy|sitcom]], ''[[Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide]]''.<ref name = "IMDB">{{cite web |url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0973974/bio |title=Devon Werkheiser at IMDB |accessdate=2007-05-20 }}</ref> 

==Personal life==
Werkheiser was born in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].  His father is a real estate executive and his mother is a homemaker. At age six he started doing impressions of actor [[Jim Carrey]] in the movie ''[[Ace Ventura Pet Detective]]''.<ref name = "IMDB"/> His parents then enrolled him in the Talent Factory, a local children's acting program, where he acted in various productions. At age 16, six years after his professional acting career started,  he and his family moved to [[Los Angeles]] to avoid having to split time between Atlanta and [[Hollywood]]. He is currently enrolled in [[Laurel Springs School]], a school that offers a long distance learning curriculum program. He is currently involved in helping local charities and is a member of the [[Starlight Starbright Children's Foundation]]. 
<ref name = "bio">{{cite web |url=http://www.devonwerkheiser.com/bio.html |title=Bio - Devon Werkheiser |accessdate=2007-05-20 }}</ref>  He is also working on a [[music album]] whose genre will be a combination of [[pop music|pop]] and [[Rock music|rock]].<ref name = "interview">{{cite web |url=http://starrymag.com/content.asp?ID=2292&CATEGORY=Interviews&PAGE=1 |title=Starry Constellation Magazine Interview |accessdate=2007-05-20 }}</ref>
Confirmed songwriter and producers for Werkheiser's album are [[Eddie Galan]] and [[Drew Lane]] of [[Trilogy Productions]]. <ref>
http://tommy2.net/content/index.php</ref>

==Acting career==
Werkheiser's first professional acting was when he was in an [[NBA]] [[Television advertisement|commercial]]. At the age of 10 he played the role of [[Mel Gibson|Mel Gibson's]] son in ''[[We Were Soldiers]]''. In 2003 he was in the TV movie ''Recipe for Disaster''. From 2004-2007 he starred in ''[[Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide]]'', his most notable role. While still on ''Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide'' he did the voice for [[Casper the Friendly Ghost|Casper]] in ''[[Casper's Scare School]]'' and played Nolan Byrd in ''[[Shredderman Rules]]''.<ref name = "bio"/>

